25|$|Benigno Aquino III {{began his}} {{presidency}} on June 30, 2010, the fifteenth President of the Philippines. He is a bachelor {{and the son}} of former Philippines president Corazon C. Aquino. His administration claimed to be focused on major reforms that would bring greater transparency, reduced poverty, reduced corruption, and a booming market which will give birth to a newly <b>industrialized</b> <b>nation.</b>|$|R
